Dialogue: 0,00:04:22.640,00:04:26.340,辉英,,0,0,0,,so the derivative so now because i wrote u as a function of not x plus ct so x plus ct
Dialogue: 0,00:04:26.340,00:04:29.380,辉英,,0,0,0,,x plus ct is x, and also t.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:29.640,00:04:31.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is x, this is t.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:32.780,00:04:34.340,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does it make sense what I'm doing?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:34.500,00:04:38.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm looking at a function of the solution along a line.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:38.700,00:04:42.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,So basically, if I make x a dependent variable of t,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:43.040,00:04:49.460,辉英,,0,0,0,,then I reduced u into a single-variate, univariate function instead of bivariate function.
