Dialogue: 0,00:05:58.540,00:05:59.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's just c, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:59.800,00:06:06.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this whole thing is equal to c times partial u, partial x plus partial u, partial t.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:06.240,00:06:09.220,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go back to the original differential equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:09.800,00:06:12.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,According to the original differential equation,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:12.220,00:06:16.900,辉英,,0,0,0,,this whole term is equal to 0 when c is equal to what?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:18.500,00:06:21.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,If c is equal to df du,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:22.440,00:06:24.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,this whole thing is going to be equal to 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:25.300,00:06:27.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,So there is a chain reaction here.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:27.780,00:06:45.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if I choose c to be equal to df du at x equal to x0 and t equal to 0,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:45.720,00:06:52.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,then I know that the time derivative of u along that line is going to be 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:52.440,00:06:57.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which means along that line, my u is going to be constant.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:58.780,00:07:02.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,My u is going to be constant tells me that c is going to be constant.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:03.580,00:07:07.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that means I can go along straight into that line
